<div class="gallery">
  <a target="_blank" href="">
    <img src="" alt="" width="600" height="400">
  </a>
  <div class="desc">Add a description of the image here</div>
</div>



// HOW TO
1) copy and paste the code above into the HTML of the page that you want the image on
2) Put the image link into the quotation marks after the href attribute and the img src attribute
3) type the needed information into the add a description of the image here such as genus, species, geolocation, etc
4) type a simple description of the image into the quotation marks after the alt term
5) you should be good after this, repeat for every image

// how to get image links from google drive
images can be put into the website by using this link
1)https://drive.google.com/thumbnail?id=imageID

2) get the image id from a shareable link from google drive, to do this you can left click on the image and presss 'get shareable link'
it should be set to be seen by everyone
https://drive.google.com/file/d/1lf8SMaHI1I_Ll5gbEan2hF_agbPDO6UF/view?usp=sharing
1lf8SMaHI1I_Ll5gbEan2hF_agbPDO6UF is the image ID
3) so paste that part into the image ID part on the first link
https://drive.google.com/thumbnail?id=1lf8SMaHI1I_Ll5gbEan2hF_agbPDO6UF
^ should look like this at the end
